g), \"[[My Old Kentucky Home]]\" (S. Foster), \"[[Comin' Thro the Rye]]\" (G. H. Clutsam), \"The Jewel Song\" (from ''[[Faust (opera)|Faust]]''), \"[[La traviata|Sempre Libera]]\" (G. Verdi), \"J'ai pleur\u00e9 en r\u00eave\" (G. H\u00fce), \"[[From the Land of the Sky-Blue Water]]\" (C. W. Cadman), \"Daddy's Sweetheart\" (L. Lehmann), and \"When I Have Sung My Songs\" (E. Charles)|| ||{{sfn|Hollywood Diva, 1998|page=351}}\n|-\n|''Jeanette MacDonald in Recital'' ||30 cities (USA)||colspan=\"2\"; align=\"center\"|Spring 1940||\" \"|| ||{{sfn|Hollywood Diva, 1998|page=351}}\n|-\n|''Jeanette MacDonald in Recital'' ||11 cities (USA)||colspan=\"2\"; align=\"center\"|Fall 1940||\" \"|| ||{{sfn|Hollywood Diva, 1998|page=351}}\n|-\n|''Jeanette MacDonald in Recital'' ||13 cities (USA)||colspan=\"2\"; align=\"center\"|Winter 1941||\" \"|| ||{{sfn|Hollywood Diva, 1998|page=351}}\n|-\n|''Jeanette MacDonald in Recital'' ||14 cities (USA)||colspan=\"2\"; align=\"center\"|Fall 1942||\" \"||For the Army Emergency Relief fund ||{{sfn|Hollywood Diva, 1998|page=351}}\n|-\n|''Jeanette MacDonald in Recital'' ||7 cities (USA)||colspan=\"2\"; align=\"center\"|Summer 1943||\" \"|| ||{{sfn|Hollywood Diva, 1998|page=351}}\n|-\n|''Jeanette MacDonald in Recital'' ||20 cities (USA)||colspan=\"2\"; align=\"center\"|Fall 1943||\" \"|| ||{{sfn|Hollywood Diva, 1998|page=351}}\n|-\n|''Jeanette MacDonald in Recital'' ||14 cities (USA)||colspan=\"2\"; align=\"center\"|Spring 1944||\" \"|| ||{{sfn|Hollywood Diva, 1998|page=351}}\n|-\n|''Jeanette MacDonald in Recital'' ||20 cities (USA)||colspan=\"2\"; align=\"center\"|Fall 1944||\" \"|| ||{{sfn|Hollywood Diva, 1998|page=351}}\n|-\n|''Jeanette MacDonald in Recital'' ||17 cities (USA)||colspan=\"2\"; align=\"center\"|Fall 1945||\" \"|| ||{{sfn|Hollywood Diva, 1998|page=351}}\n|-\n|''Jeanette MacDonald in Recital'' ||England, Scotland and Wales (7 cities)||colspan=\"2\"; align=\"center\"|Summer 1946||\" \"||It was roughly at this point when other songs we