he Lost Manuscript]]|publisher=Bell Harbour Press|year=2004|isbn=0-9711998-8-4}} The complete, typewritten autobiography with MacDonald's handwritten editing, deletions and comments noted throughout. Annotated and with original letters from MacDonald's collaborator on the project.\n*{{cite book|last=Rich|first=Sharon|title=[[Nelson Eddy: The Opera Years]]|publisher=Bell Harbour Press |year=2001|isbn=0-9711998-0-9}}\n*{{cite book|last=Rich|first=Sharon|title=[[Sweethearts: The Timeless Love Affair Onscreen and Off Between Jeanette MacDonald and Nelson Eddy]]|date=2001|publisher=Bell Harbour Press|isbn= 0-9711998-1-7}} This is an updated edition of Rich, Sharon, ''Sweethearts: The Timeless Love Affair - On-screen and Off - Between Jeanette MacDonald and Nelson Eddy'', Donald I. Fine, 1994. Footnotes are from 2001 edition. Updated again in 2014.\n*{{citebook|last=Turk|first=Edward Baron|author-link=Edward Baron Turk|title=Hollywood Diva: A Biography of Jeanette MacDonald|url=https://archive.org/details/hollywooddivabio0000turk|url-access=registration|publisher=[[University of California Press]]|year=1998|isbn=978-0-520-22253-3|ref={{sfnRef|Hollywood Diva, 1998}}}}\n* {{cite book|title=I'll See You Again: The Bittersweet Love Story and Wartime Letters of Jeanette MacDonald and Gene Raymond, Volume 1: The War - and Before|first=Maggie|last= McCormick|subject-link=Maggie McCormick|publisher=BearManor Media|year=2019|isbn=978-1-62933-436-3|ref={{sfnRef|I'll See You Again, 2019}}}}\n* {{cite book|title=I'll See You Again: The Bittersweet Love Story and Wartime Letters of Jeanette MacDonald and Gene Raymond, Volume 2: The Letters|first=Maggie|last= McCormick|subject-link=Maggie McCormick|publisher=BearManor Media|year=2019|isbn=978-1-62933-448-6|ref={{sfnRef|I'll See You Again, 2019}}}}\n* {{cite book|title=I'll See You Again: The Bittersweet Love Story and Wartime Letters of Jeanette MacDonald and Gene Raymond, Volume 3: After the War|first=Maggie|last= McCormick|subject-link=Maggie McCormick|publisher=BearManor Media|year=2019|isbn=978-1-62933-450-9|ref={{sfnRef|I'll See You Again, 2019}}}}\n\n==External links==\n{{Portal bar|Biography|Film|Music|Theatre|Opera}}\n{{Commons}}\n* {{IMDb name|531776}}\n* {{IBDB name|68162}}\n* {{Find a Grave|1335}}\n* {{Tcmdb name|118611}}\n\n{{Jeanette MacDonald}}\n{{Authority control}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Macdonald, Jeanette}}\n[[Category:1903 births]]\n[[Category:1965 deaths]]\n[[Category:American film actresses]]\n[[Category:American musical theatre actresses]]\n[[Category:American operatic sopranos]]\n[[Category:American people of Scottish descent]]\n[[Category:Musicians from Philadelphia]]\n[[Category:Actresses from Philadelphia]]\n[[Category:Vaudeville performers]]\n[[Category:Burials at Forest Lawn Memorial Park (Glendale)]]\n[[Category:Metro-Goldwyn-Mayer contract players]]\n[[Category:20th-century American actresses]]\n[[Category:Paramount Pictures contract players]]\n[[Category:20th-century American opera singers]]\n[[Category:20th-century women opera singers]]\n[[Category:Singers from Pennsylvania]]\n[[Category:American people of Dutch descent]]\n[[Category:American people of English descent]]\n[[Category:California Republicans]]\n[[Category:Pennsylvania Republicans]]\n[[Category:RCA Records artists]]\n[[Category:Texas Republicans]]\n[[Category:20th-century American women singers]]\n[[Category:Classical musicians from Pennsylvania]]\n[[Category:American sopranos]]\n", "name_user": "Tiptopper", "label": "safe", "comment": "American Women's Voluntary Services, renamed, and linked", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Jeanette_MacDonald"}
